        Creating a MagStripeData object with data.
        Parameters:
        trackData - The scanned data in string format (encrypted or unencrypted).
        maskedTrackData - The scanned data in string format, with private data masked out (if trackData is encrypted).
        rawData - data in raw form
        isTrackDataEncrypted - true if encrypted else false
        isGoodSwipe - true if the swipe is valid else false

    • Method Detail

      • getTrackData

        public java.lang.String getTrackData(int trackNumber)
        Get encrypted or unencrypted track data selected with trackNumber. If isTrackDataEncrypted() then the returned data is in encrypted form - please consult the hardware vendor on the method of decrypting track data. Otherwise the track data is not encrypted.
        Parameters:
        trackNumber - The track number to get. Either 1, 2 or 3.
        Returns:
        Track data selected with trackNumber in String format
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the trackNumber is invalid

      • getMaskedTrackData

        public java.lang.String getMaskedTrackData(int trackNumber)
        Get masked track data selected with trackNumber. If isTrackDataEncrypted() then this returns the track data with private information masked out with replacement character (e.g. credit card number). Otherwise if track data is not encrypted, you should use getTrackData(int) instead - this method return null.
        Parameters:
        trackNumber - The track number to get. Either 1, 2 or 3.
        Returns:
        Masked track data selected with trackNumber in String format. That data is included start sentinel (ex. %, ; ).
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the trackNumber is invalid

      • getRawData

        public byte[] getRawData()

        Returns:
        the data as scanned from the magstripe reader.

      • isTrackDataEncrypted

        public boolean isTrackDataEncrypted()
        Returns true if track data is encrypted.
        Returns:
        True if track data is encrypted.

      • isGoodSwipe

        public boolean isGoodSwipe()
        Determines if scanned data is valid. I.e. if the track data has passed the hash code validation and contains no errors.
        Returns:
        true if scanned data is valid, otherwise false.
